    "summary": "After being submerged in the Amsterdam ad scene for seven years, Mark waved goodbye to his job as a copywriter, tossed his home into a backpack, and hit the world as\u00a0\u00a0\u2018The Backpacker Intern\u2018, helping out agencies, brands, and charities in exchange for room and board.\u00a0\n\u00a0\nThe journey has brought him to 27 countries on 7 continents where he worked at 32 companies such as TBWA\\Chiat\\Day LA, Red Bull HQ Austria, UNICEF New Zealand, Ogilvy Cape Town, Amnesty International Thailand, and JWT Buenos Aires.\n\u00a0\nMark worked with Grammy Award winner Nile Rodgers, helped out ex-drug traffickers in the favelas of Rio, and even landed a job on the coldest continent of the world; Antarctica. It gave him a global perspective and planted the seed to travel within to explore the concepts of consciousness and awareness.\u00a0 \n\u00a0\n\u2028In February 2016 Mark co-founded\u00a0Wanderbrief, a platform that makes the Digital Nomad life easy. Wanderbrief has grown into a community of thousands of professionals from 100 countries working with companies such as WeWork, Selina, and Adobe.\n\u00a0\nIn February 2020 Wanderbrief was\u00a0acquired by Unsettled. Mark joined the Board of Advisors to help Unsettled grow their network and business.\n\u00a0\nMark is an experienced Motivational Speaker at events all over the planet, who takes audiences worldwide on a spectacular journey within. +200 events around the globe, including TEDx, SXSW, Cannes Lions, Adidas HQ, Booking HQ, and the United Nations in NYC.\n\nHe was recognized by The White House as Top 100 Most Influential Travel Blogger In The World. His work has been featured in: Adweek, MTV, Entrepreneur, Mashable, and many other major media outlets.\n\nMark's trips around the world (59 countries, 7 continents) have opened his eyes and mind to go on the journey within. Besides his daily Transcendental Meditation practice he studies all forms of Philosophy, (Self)Awareness, Yoga, Breath work, Meditation, Sound Healing, Ancient Wisdom, and the Science of Well-Being to live a more conscious life.\n\nNow, Mark is applying all the experiences, insights and his passion for music into 'Sound Alchemy'. Designing immersive Soundjourneys for people, brands and organisations to enhance well-being. His intention is to bring the world in harmony through Music, Wisdom & Well-being.\n\nNext to that he is the co-founder of Mmm Cacao, a conscious company on a mission to re-connect the hearts and minds of humanity. They offer cacao, cacao circles and soundjourneys. \n\nIn his free time you can catch him performing and sharing his own music as 'Mark Peace' at events, ceremonies and festivals.",
